WEBVTT

00:01.948 --> 00:05.063
- <i>Previously on</i> Gotham...
- Watch out! (screams)

00:05.113 --> 00:06.180
SELINA: <i>Ivy's missing.</i>

00:06.248 --> 00:07.214
She'll turn up somewhere.

00:07.282 --> 00:09.450
It was a long way down into water.

00:09.518 --> 00:11.318
MARV: What's your name? My name's Ivy.

00:12.767 --> 00:14.188
- Who the hell are you?
- Not yet.

00:14.256 --> 00:15.923
This is too fun.

00:15.991 --> 00:18.826
ISABELLA: <i>He loves me and I love him.</i>

00:18.894 --> 00:20.261
OSWALD: <i>I am telling you one last time,</i>

00:20.328 --> 00:23.163
let Ed go.

00:23.231 --> 00:24.598
- No.
- Very well.

00:24.666 --> 00:25.933
<i>Don't say I didn't warn you.</i>

00:26.001 --> 00:27.401
Oh, no.

00:28.770 --> 00:30.905
(screaming): Somebody help!

00:30.972 --> 00:32.573
I want to rejoin the GCPD.

00:32.641 --> 00:34.808
Welcome back, Detective.

00:34.876 --> 00:36.143
Captain, I'm so glad you came.

00:36.211 --> 00:38.178
I came to congratulate you.

00:38.246 --> 00:41.682
ALICE: <i>If a person comes into contact
with my blood, it changes them.</i>

00:41.750 --> 00:43.183
BARNES: <i>You and I are gonna
make a difference in this city.</i>

00:43.251 --> 00:44.251
<i>We're gonna clean it up.</i>

00:44.319 --> 00:46.387
(screaming)

00:49.090 --> 00:51.325
<i>Sentence served.</i>

00:51.393 --> 00:53.994
Symon. (groaning)

00:54.062 --> 00:55.129
Who did this?

00:55.196 --> 00:56.964
Barnes.

01:01.202 --> 01:03.671
(indistinct chatter)

01:03.738 --> 01:05.438
CAMPOS: So, seems anyone
could have gotten access

01:05.507 --> 01:06.707
to that bathroom, not just the guests.

01:06.775 --> 01:08.075
Suspect pool's wide open.

01:08.143 --> 01:09.143
All right, start with statements

01:09.210 --> 01:10.578
from everyone at the party.

01:10.645 --> 01:12.276
Someone saw Symon go into that bathroom.

01:12.338 --> 01:13.604
Okay.

01:16.684 --> 01:17.985
I still can't believe it.

01:18.052 --> 01:20.320
I'm sorry things went down this way.

01:20.388 --> 01:21.822
Don't apologize; you were right.

01:21.890 --> 01:23.857
Did you give your statement already?

01:23.925 --> 01:25.492
I'm afraid I wasn't very helpful.

01:25.560 --> 01:27.928
Till about an hour ago,
I couldn't pick Symon

01:27.996 --> 01:29.029
out of a crowd.

01:29.097 --> 01:31.465
Did you talk to Barnes at the party?

01:31.533 --> 01:34.701
A little. We had a drink.

01:34.769 --> 01:37.237
Symon died around 10:30.

01:37.305 --> 01:38.705
The attack happened just before.

01:38.773 --> 01:40.140
What time did you talk with Barnes?

01:40.208 --> 01:41.375
9:00.

01:41.442 --> 01:43.844
What is this about?

01:45.146 --> 01:47.748
- (sighs) Nothing.
- Nothing? Really?

01:47.816 --> 01:49.483
I can't talk about it.

01:49.551 --> 01:51.451
No.

01:51.519 --> 01:52.853
Lee, I cannot talk about it.

01:52.921 --> 01:55.055
Jim, I hope you know what you're doing.

01:55.123 --> 01:57.324
Me, too.

01:57.392 --> 01:58.892
Barnes? No. No, no, no, no, no.

01:58.960 --> 02:00.394
I asked Symon who attacked him,

02:00.461 --> 02:01.695
and he said Barnes.

02:01.763 --> 02:03.363
Symon was a psychopath

02:03.431 --> 02:05.365
who gave face transplants to the mob

02:05.433 --> 02:06.733
using stolen faces.

02:06.801 --> 02:08.134
Hardly a credible witness.

02:08.203 --> 02:09.269
And this guy, Barnes?

02:09.336 --> 02:10.770
If he so much as jaywalked,

02:10.839 --> 02:13.140
- he would write himself a ticket.
- I know.

02:13.208 --> 02:15.209
"And now you're saying
he went to Lee Thompkin"

02:15.276 --> 02:17.778
engagement party, and out of
nowhere, busted some guy's face

02:17.846 --> 02:20.147
and chucked him through a wall?
- I know, Harvey.

02:20.215 --> 02:22.783
- What's the motive?
- I don't know, maybe he...

02:22.851 --> 02:24.151
He saw Symon,

02:24.219 --> 02:25.252
he got pissed he was released,

02:25.320 --> 02:26.787
and he lost control.

02:26.855 --> 02:28.488
Okay. So, you're saying

02:28.556 --> 02:30.691
that a man with a
spotless 20-year career,

02:30.758 --> 02:32.759
just went ape. Is-is that your theory?

02:32.827 --> 02:34.761
Something's been off about him recently.

02:34.829 --> 02:37.064
You yourself said he
nearly beat Tetch to death.

02:37.131 --> 02:39.733
And what's with him
insisting on running point

02:39.801 --> 02:41.335
- in the Paulie Pennies case?
- Look,

02:41.402 --> 02:43.537
I don't know, but that
does not make him a killer.

02:43.605 --> 02:45.472
So where is he now?

02:45.540 --> 02:47.708
Home. He spent the
better part of yesterday

02:47.775 --> 02:50.010
chasing down Symon, maybe he's tired.

02:50.078 --> 02:51.778
That doesn't mean he's guilty.

02:51.846 --> 02:55.115
The last thing I want is
for Barnes to be guilty.

02:55.183 --> 02:56.316
I look up to the man.

02:56.384 --> 02:59.019
But if there is even a
chance then we have to know.

02:59.087 --> 03:00.954
And something doesn't feel right.

03:01.022 --> 03:04.057
Okay, okay, okay. I'm gonna help you.

03:04.125 --> 03:06.360
But just so you know,
I'm doing it to prove

03:06.427 --> 03:08.061
he's innocent, not guilty.

03:08.129 --> 03:09.997
That's fine. All right, so
I'll go back to the scene,

03:10.064 --> 03:12.699
see if forensics can pull
some prints from the bathroom.

03:12.767 --> 03:14.635
Barnes's should already be on file.

03:14.702 --> 03:17.771
Jim. I know how to do my job.

03:19.307 --> 03:21.208
I hope I'm wrong.

03:21.276 --> 03:24.611
Yeah. Me, too.

03:29.784 --> 03:32.519
(sirens wailing in distance)

03:32.587 --> 03:34.554
(grunting)

03:34.622 --> 03:37.024
(foghorn blowing)

03:37.091 --> 03:40.127
It starts as a whisper.

03:40.194 --> 03:42.095
You have to strain to hear it.

03:42.163 --> 03:43.797
(muffled whimpering)

03:43.865 --> 03:48.201
And then it grows louder and louder,

03:48.269 --> 03:51.605
till it becomes a roar.

03:51.673 --> 03:55.509
It's everything you can
do to just shut it out.

03:57.178 --> 03:58.712
And just like that...

03:58.780 --> 04:01.682
you suddenly realize it's <i>your</i> voice.

04:01.749 --> 04:04.451
The one you've been denying.

04:04.519 --> 04:06.386
Telling you who you are.

04:08.122 --> 04:10.190
What you have to do.

04:10.258 --> 04:12.426
And then you stop fighting.

04:14.729 --> 04:16.897
And this calm comes over you.

04:16.964 --> 04:18.665
(muffled groaning)

04:23.638 --> 04:26.106
(whimpering and groaning continue)

04:28.343 --> 04:30.644
Sex trafficking.

04:31.913 --> 04:33.513
Drugs.

04:34.415 --> 04:36.216
Murder.

04:36.284 --> 04:40.320
I've kept files on all
three of you for years.

04:40.388 --> 04:42.089
Waiting for the proof we needed

04:42.156 --> 04:44.825
while you sneered at the law.

04:44.892 --> 04:46.460
Not tonight.

04:48.496 --> 04:50.430
Tonight, I <i>am</i> the law!

04:52.767 --> 04:55.202
And you are hereby tried.

04:55.269 --> 04:57.904
(crunches, groaning)

04:57.972 --> 04:59.806
Found guilty.

05:02.410 --> 05:04.745
And sentenced.

